answersResultList.title: Not very Sagittarius.
answersResultList.resultContent: You're not very comfortable with change, and that's not very Sagittarius of you. You're a big thinker who prefers to have adventures of the mind instead of exploring the real world. An expert at taking care of life's necessities, you're unlikely to go out on a limb for something you don't really need. After your friends do wild, impossible things, you invite them to your house so they can tell you all about it. Your best romantic match is someone a little timid who hangs on your every word. A bolder or more independent lover would probably make you crazy.

answersResultList.title: Somewhat Sagittarius.
answersResultList.resultContent: The rules are important to you. You might bend one or two of them after carefully checking out all the options, but usually you'll stick to your appointed path. The idea of change interests you, and that's somewhat Sagittarius, but follow-through can be messy, and you often end up backing away and making excuses. You're one of the most organized, punctual people you know, which means you're surrounded by flakes and fools. Sometimes you lash out at them, but mostly you grumble and remain patient. When you can laugh at these inconveniences, that's a Sagittarian trait right there.

answersResultList.title: Mostly Sagittarius.
answersResultList.resultContent: You enjoy traveling without a map, working without a net, and generally pushing your luck - all signs of a true Sagittarius. But once the adventure is over, you like returning to your safe, stable life. While you're a big fan of necessary change, the point of when it's necessary is always up for debate. Procrastination isn't a Sagittarian quality, although the Archer does love a good, heated argument. That's why you're likely to surround yourself with people who are always challenging each other. You keep them smiling and laughing, especially when they follow you willingly on the next big adventure.

The idea of change interests you, and that's somewhat Sagittarius, but follow-through can be messy, and you often end up backing away and making excuses. You're one of the most organized, punctual people you know, which means you're surrounded by flakes and fools. Sometimes you lash out at them, but mostly you grumble and remain patient. When you can laugh at these inconveniences, that's a Sagittarian trait right there.

answersResultList.title: Mostly Sagittarius.
answersResultList.resultContent: You enjoy traveling without a map, working without a net, and generally pushing your luck - all signs of a true Sagittarius. But once the adventure is over, you like returning to your safe, stable life. While you're a big fan of necessary change, the point of when it's necessary is always up for debate. Procrastination isn't a Sagittarian quality, although the Archer does love a good, heated argument. That's why you're likely to surround yourself with people who are always challenging each other. You keep them smiling and laughing, especially when they follow you willingly on the next big adventure.

answersResultList.title: Not very Sagittarius.
answersResultList.resultContent: You're not very comfortable with change, and that's not very Sagittarius of you. You're a big thinker who prefers to have adventures of the mind instead of exploring the real world. An expert at taking care of life's necessities, you're unlikely to go out on a limb for something you don't really need. After your friends do wild, impossible things, you invite them to your house so they can tell you all about it. Your best romantic match is someone a little timid who hangs on your every word. A bolder or more independent lover would probably make you crazy.
